TITLE: Defining Conditional Abilities for Blog Permissions in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how to define more complex abilities with conditions, such as allowing users to update their own articles and comments.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stalniy/casl/blob/master/docs-src/src/content/pages/guide/intro/en.md#2025-04-17_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { defineAbility } from '@casl/ability';

export default (user) => defineAbility((can) => {
  can('read', 'Article');

  if (user.isLoggedIn) {
    can('update', 'Article', { authorId: user.id });
    can('create', 'Comment');
    can('update', 'Comment', { authorId: user.id });
  }
});
```

