TITLE: Embedding CASL Ability Rules in JWT Token Payload
DESCRIPTION: Implementation of a login handler that embeds ability rules in JWT token payload. This approach is suitable for stateless applications using JWT authentication.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stalniy/casl/blob/master/docs-src/src/content/pages/cookbook/cache-rules/en.md#2025-04-17_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import jwt from 'jsonwebtoken';
import { defineRulesFor } from './defineAbility';

export async function login(req, res) {
  const token = jwt.sign({
    id: req.user.id,
    rules: await defineRulesFor(req.user)
  }, 'secret', { expiresIn: '1d' })

  res.send({ token })
}
```

