TITLE: Integrating accessibleFieldsPlugin with Mongoose and TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to extend a Mongoose model with the accessibleFieldsPlugin to add accessibleFieldsBy methods to both the model and document instances. This allows for field-level access control.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stalniy/casl/blob/master/packages/casl-mongoose/README.md#2025-04-17_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import {
  accessibleFieldsPlugin,
  AccessibleFieldsModel,
  AccessibleFieldsDocument
} from '@casl/mongoose';
import * as mongoose from 'mongoose';

export interface Post extends AccessibleFieldsDocument {
  // the same Post definition from previous example
}

const PostSchema = new mongoose.Schema<Post>({
  // the same Post schema definition from previous example
})

PostSchema.plugin(accessibleFieldsPlugin);

export const Post = mongoose.model<Post, AccessibleFieldsModel<Post>>('Post', PostSchema);

// Now we can safely use `Post.accessibleFieldsBy` method and `post.accessibleFieldsBy`
Post.accessibleFieldsBy(/* parameters */);
const post = new Post();
post.accessibleFieldsBy(/* parameters */);
```

